  <title>The Main Toolbar</title>
  <p>
    The main toolbar above initially looks like this:
  </p>
  <media type="image" mime="src/png" src="figures/main-toolbar-disconnected.png">
    <p>The Main Toolbar When Disconnected</p>
  </media>
  <p>Für jede Funktion gibt es einen Hinweistext, der angezeigt wird, wenn der Mauszeiger eine Zeitlang über dem jeweiligen Button ruht. Die Buttons von links nach rechts sind:</p>
  <list type="numbered">
    <item>
      <p>Connect</p>
      <p>
        Click to <link xref="connect">connect</link>, you guessed it.
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Status</p>
      <p>
        This button has no function, while you are disconnected.
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Quit</p>
      <p>
        Click to terminate the program.
      </p>
    </item>
  </list>
  <p>
    Once you are <link xref="connect">connected</link> to a server,
    the toolbar rather looks like this:
  </p>
  <media type="image" mime="src/png" src="figures/main-toolbar-connected.png">
    <p>The Main Toolbar When Connected</p>
  </media>
  <list type="numbered">
    <item>
      <p>Disonnect</p>
      <p>
        Click to <link xref="connect">disconnect</link>.  This will
        terminate your ongoing match.  The server will save your match
        but normally you should play your matches to the end before
        you disconnect.
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Status</p>
      <p>
        In the above screenshot, your status is <gui style="label">Ready</gui>,
        that means you are available for playing and other people can invite you 
        to matches.  Clicking it will toggle your state to
        <gui style="label">Not Ready</gui> and you can neither get invited
        or invite other people.
      </p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Quit</p>
      <p>
        Click to terminate the program.  That will also
        terminate your ongoing match.  The server will save your match
        but normally you should play your matches to the end before
        you disconnect.
      </p>
    </item>
  </list>
